                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	Jungle Crows defeated Delhi Lions 40-12 in a Losers Plate match of the 77th All India amp; South Asia Rugby Tournament, at the CC amp;FC, on Monday. In the other matches, CC amp;FC beat Bombay Gymkhana 20-8, while Kolkata Police trounced Bangalore 25-8.          
	The Bengal team selection for the Moin-ud-Dowlah Trophy will take place on September 3. Bengal will play their first match against Rajasthan on September 11-12. The second match, against UP, is on September 15-16 and the final, on September 21-23.                
	Football: CFL Premier Division  East Bengal vs Mohammedan AC (East Bengal ground); WB Police vs Aryan (at the Barasat Stadium); George Telegraph vs Eastern Railway (Salt Lake Stadium). All matches from 3.30pm      
